org.docheinstein.mp3doctor.ui.main

Class MainWindowController.Category

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.docheinstein.mp3doctor.ui.main.MainWindowController.Category
  • Enclosing class:
    MainWindowController

    private abstract static class MainWindowController.Category
extends java.lang.Object
    Entity that represents a category which essentially is a controller mController and its view mNode.

    Furthermore, this entity is responsible for provide a title and a category label (which actually is the row that contains the category name on the left side panel)

    The category entity keeps track even of the validity of its controller: if the controller is valid (not marked as dirty via markAsDirty()) then when the user changes category and returns to that valid controller, no action is done.

    Although, if the controller is not valid (marked as dirty via markAsDirty(), then a reinitialization of the controller can be required before show the controller via Reinitializable.reinit(), which must be implemented by the controller this entity wraps.

      • markAsDirty

        public void markAsDirty()
        Marks the category as dirty (it can be used when the underlying model of the controller changes and thus it must be reinitialized).

        Using this method implies that when the getNode() is called it will invoke Reinitializable.reinit() for the controller (only once).

        Note that this action has effect only if a node has already been created, otherwise there is nothing to mark as dirty.

      • initIfDirty

        private void initIfDirty()
        Calls Reinitializable.reinit() if this category is dirty, and if so, marks this category as not dirty anymore.
